subject: Jane Jane that is wildly simplistic.
body: And we both know the situation is far more complex than that! Yes you are correct and a proportion of homeless people do you have a drink and drugs problem, and I do get help, and then they are turned away from hospital accommodation because they cannot get over there drinking drug problems. But I’ve met a vast amount of homeless people that actually hold down daytime jobs - but just can’t get out of the ‘loop’ of what they need which is a bank account and an address in order to get accommodation/and/or a decent job.

subject: I will be at the UCL MechSpace opposite Kings Cross on Wednesday 17th May, offering FREE 3D printed repairs with Morley Kert!
body:
Bring your broken lamp, vacuum cleaner, umbrella, drill, tool box, bicycle, stroller, typewriter, tripod, coffee maker, glasses, binoculars, chair, keyboard, or whatever else and we will design AND 3D print a custom repair for it on the spot!

We will also be offering 3D printed improvements for unbroken items.

Curious about what sort of 3D printed repairs we can do? Check out videos of Morley’s past repair days here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL0yOCIERwTxg3RucVhshTsecl4su9X8gj

Here are links to our YouTube channels:
Morley: https://www.youtube.com/@MorleyKert
Matt: https://www.youtube.com/@MattGrayYES
author: M. G.

subject: Is London all bad?
body:
I am reading post after post of negative interactions or incidents between Londoners and it is heart breaking to read. 
I know times are tough at the moment but surely London is not all bad? 

Let’s share some positive stories about the beauty of London and it’s people. 
I’ll start by thanking the lovely Lady at Walthamstow Central Station who chased me down to hand me the £10 that fell out of my bag without me even knowing ❤️. I am so grateful. 

Join me is sharing your lovely stories. Hopefully we can uplift each others day, give each other hope and share joy during these trying times. ❤️

subject: Hi, I'm Vlad. 👋 Nice to meet you.
body:
Hi everyone👋 i’m Vlad, new to the app and quite enthused to have found out about it. I recently moved to the area with my 2 housemates and 3 funny little dogs.

I love it allready, though i find one thing Soho’s missing is that bit of community feel. Amongst the bunch of eclectic things i’m passionate about, i’d have to mention music, that’s always been a big part of my life, social events, culture and awareness in a spirit of empathy and growth. I appreciate good design, creativity, humbleness and general willingness to ipmrove.

I party, ride vintage steel road bikes, I am interested in art and the stimulating intelectual and cultural aspects London offers in abbundance. I practiced and thought a style of japanese martial arts, now I practice a type of therapeutic massage [fully clothed😁] and get satisfaction from helping people out.

Awful at monologues & describing myself (..obviously😅)

Regards to everyone. Keep doing good & let’s keep it together😇🤗
1!

subject: I'm looking for a self-contained flat or studio for my brother, for immediate occupancy.
body: He's 65 years old, receives Pension and Pension Credit, and has the usual deposit and rent in advance available. He needs this accommodation following the death of our 86-year-old father, with whom he was living, and the local authority's refusal to allow him to succeed to the tenancy of our father's (much too large) house. We are available to view immediately and to move in within days if required. He is currently staying with family members in a flat that's far too small, so an early move would be best.

subject: Hi all, our car was broken into and a black backpack was stolen on 8th December 2022 at 5:50pm in Q park Soho.
body:
The man dressed in high vis jacket and a blue trousers with reflective stripes. The outfit is highly similar to a Westminster council street cleaner/sanitation worker. He was wearing a beanie. He was also carrying a black backpack and a black laptop bag. It could be that he also committed other crime in the area. 
If this sounds familiar to anyone, if your backpack/ laptop bag was stolen on the same bag, or if you have noticed a man like that. Please give us a shout :)
